snippet.textDisplay:
Tappe(plural) is a kind of Punjabi song/music played at an event. Its a mix of folk but fast-paced and melodious.
Nowadays they are sung at weddings, childbirth, loved one leaving or reunion after a long time.  The tradition can be found in Punjabi Speaking families and more common in the villages. 
Nice Job Coke Studio :)
